<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-06-11T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-06-11T00:00:00-05:00" n="202" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d202">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 893.51/933.</note>
                            <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-06-11">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 11, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Sir Edward Grey thinks it would be a mistake to move about the
                                question of Mongolia and Manchuria until he hears from the Russian
                                and Japanese Governments.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Reid.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>